This paper proposes a novel framework for federated learning with differential privacy and analyzes its convergence performance and privacy protection levels. The paper focuses on machine learning and privacy, which are core topics in the computer science field. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
